gomodel:SYNGO_1985  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7+8: Authors look at the effect of EtOH exposure on expression and presynaptic localization of the nACHR alpha4 subunit in dopaminergic nerve terminals in the nucleus accumbens. Localization is assessed with a alpha4-GFP knock-in mouse model. Authors quantified presynaptic localization by measuring colocalization of GFP-alpha4 with the presynaptic marker synaptophysin withing HT-positive terminals.\n\n27/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - Tissue is of mouse species: \"The α4 nAChR YFP knock-in mice were produced by replacing ...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1985" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

